      "content": "it didnt feel metaphorical at all. it felt digital. like a literal bio-electric signal. if you look at how HFT works, they're basically just processing massive amounts of data via electrical signals in fiber optics and microwave towers. if my nervous system is sensitive enough, could there actually be some kind of electromagnetic resonance happening? like, the sheer volume of data moving through the infrastructure creates a field that my body is physically picking up on? it feels way more plausible than just \"stress.\"",
